                <div class="work-description">
                    <h2>About The Piece</h2>
                    <p>“Artificial Meadow” was created for a drawing assignment that challenged us to build a landscape from an arrangement of everyday household objects. I used a scarf, crystals, coverup fabric, and paper to create a small staged scene, then reinterpreted it as a surreal fieldscape through drawing.</p>
                    <p>Colored pencil was the medium of choice to amplify texture and bring out vivid, unnatural hues. The swirling sky and dense blades of grass were imagined from folds, fibers, and surface details in the fabric, pushing ordinary textures into an otherworldly environment.</p>
                    <p>This piece plays with perception—turning overlooked objects into the foundation for a dreamlike world. “Artificial Meadow” explores the magic that can emerge when we view the familiar through a transformed lens.</p>
